<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36205f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36205f">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36205f"> 205(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Kykloks</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Ku Kluxism.]</font> Among the names suggested was &ldquo;<mark>Kukloi</mark>,&rdquo; the plural of &ldquo;Kuklos,&rdquo; the Greek word for circle. &ldquo;Ku Klux&rdquo;&mdash;a barbarization of the word Kuklos&mdash;was suggested and at once adopted. The word Klan was of course added to carry out the alliteration, and soon the name Ku Klux Klan got into currency. <small> Charles W. Ferguson, <a name="CFCT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CFCT"><cite title="source">The Confusion of Tongues</cite></a> (1928; rpt. May 1929) 256</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
